.TH DEFINE "1" "December 2025" "define 202409241930-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
define \- Dictionary lookup using curl and Free Dictionary API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B define
[\\fI\\,OPTIONS\\/\\fR] [\\fI\\,COMMAND\\/\\fR] [\\fI\\,WORD\\/\\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B define
is a dictionary lookup tool that uses curl to query online dictionary APIs for word definitions, etymology, and similar words. It requires only curl and provides formatted output directly in the terminal or optionally in graphical dialogs.
.PP
The script uses the Free Dictionary API (dictionaryapi.dev) for definitions, Datamuse API for finding similar words, and etymonline.com for etymology lookups. Results are cached locally for faster subsequent lookups.
.PP
A custom API URL can be configured via the DEFINE_API_URL environment variable or configuration file, allowing use of alternative dictionary services.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B define [word]
Get definition from the Free Dictionary API, displaying part of speech and definitions
.TP
.B define multiple [word]
Full lookup showing all parts of speech and definitions for the word
.TP
.B define etymology [word]
Get word etymology and origin information from etymonline.com
.TP
.B define cached [word]
Use cached definitions for faster lookups. Caches definitions for 24 hours by default
.TP
.B define similar [word]
Find words similar to the search term using Datamuse API
.TP
.B define clear-cache
Clear all cached word definitions to force fresh lookups
