.SH APIS USED
.SS Free Dictionary API (dictionaryapi.dev)
Primary API for word definitions. Returns JSON with:
.RS
.IP \\(bu 2
Word meanings organized by part of speech
.IP \\(bu 2
Multiple definitions per part of speech
.IP \\(bu 2
Phonetic pronunciation information
.IP \\(bu 2
Example usage and synonyms
.RE
.PP
Default endpoint: https://api.dictionaryapi.dev/api/v2/entries/en/{word}
.SS Datamuse API
Used for finding similar words and suggestions:
.RS
.IP \\(bu 2
Spelling suggestions
.IP \\(bu 2
Words starting with prefix
.IP \\(bu 2
Related words and synonyms
.RE
.PP
Endpoint: https://api.datamuse.com/words?sp={word}*&max=10
.SS Etymonline.com
Used for etymology lookups:
.RS
.IP \\(bu 2
Word origins and history
.IP \\(bu 2
Historical usage development
.IP \\(bu 2
Related word families
.RE
.PP
Endpoint: https://www.etymonline.com/word/{word}
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
Definitions are formatted with:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
word (part of speech):
 1. First definition
 2. Second definition
 3. Third definition
.EE
.RE
.PP
Up to 5 definitions are shown per part of speech to keep output readable.
.SH GUI INTEGRATION
When --gtk option is used or GUI is requested, define will attempt to use graphical dialog tools:
.SS Supported GUI Tools
.TP
.B yad
Yet Another Dialog - modern dialog replacement with rich features (preferred)
.TP
.B zenity
Display GTK+ dialogs from command line (fallback)
.PP
GUI dialogs require:
.RS
.IP \\(bu 2
X11 display available ($DISPLAY set)
.IP \\(bu 2
Not connected via SSH (no $SSH_CONNECTION)
.IP \\(bu 2
yad or zenity installed
.RE
.PP
If GUI requirements aren't met, output falls back to terminal with color formatting.
.SH CACHING
Define implements local caching to improve performance and reduce API requests:
.PP
.RS 4
.B Cache Location:
~/.cache/define/
.PP
.B Cache Duration:
24 hours (86400 seconds) default
.PP
.B Cache Files:
One file per word: <word>.cache
.PP
.B Cache Behavior:
.RS
.IP \\(bu 2
Fresh lookup if cache missing or expired
.IP \\(bu 2
Automatic cache on successful lookup
.IP \\(bu 2
Manual cache clearing with clear-cache command
.RE
.RE
